50|$|The Federal Estate Tax was {{introduced}} in 1916, and Gift Tax in 1924. Unlike many <b>inheritance</b> <b>taxes,</b> the Gift and Estate taxes were imposed on the transferor rather than the recipient. Many states adopted either <b>inheritance</b> <b>taxes</b> or estate and gift taxes, often computed as the amount allowed as a deduction for federal purposes. These taxes remained under 1% of government revenues through the 1990s.|$|R
